@surajnarwade that's probably right.
`Docker` is storing the images in `/var/lib/docker/<storagename>` by default.
For example, since my storage driver is `overlay2` then the images are stored under `/var/lib/docker/overlay2`.
Even if I try to read from that directory in order to list images, it's likely that the way the images are stored is not according to `OCI` and therefore `buildah` won't be able to list them.

@rhatdan correct me if I'm wrong.
